<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2291] closure parameter default value</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2291</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def yyy = 555

def boo = {&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; x = yyy -&amp;gt; println x}

boo()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running this script result in&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException: No such property: yyy for class: Boo&lt;br/&gt;
at Boo.boo(Boo.groovy)&lt;br/&gt;
at Boo.run(Boo.groovy:1)&lt;br/&gt;
at Boo.main(Boo.groovy)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Closure parameter default value should be able to reference local context, not just the properties of the class&lt;/p&gt;</description>
